### MVC vs MVP vs MVVM

MVC couples View and Controller tightly; MVP adds a Presenter to handle all View logic, making Views testable; MVVM uses two-way data binding between View and ViewModel for reactive updates. Use MVC for simple apps, MVP for complex UI logic requiring testability, and MVVM for reactive frameworks like Vue or Angular with automatic synchronization.

```typescript
// MVVM Example (Vue-like)
class UserViewModel {
  users = ref([]);
  selectedUser = ref(null);

  selectUser(id: string) {
    this.selectedUser.value = this.users.value.find(u => u.id === id);
  }
}

// View auto-updates when selectedUser changes
<div>{{ viewModel.selectedUser.value?.name }}</div>
```

**Common interview trap:** Claiming MVP is always better for testability without considering development complexity or team size.

